Controls how many server messages you receive. Higher level = more messages; lower level = fewer. Your setting is saved with your character. Default is 10.

If no parameters are set, the current listen level is shown:

listen
  Set listen to what (presently 10)?

If a numeric listen level is specified (i.e., 10), the following message is the output:

listen 10
  Your verbose level is now 10.

Listen Levels:

  Level 0   = Nothing. Private tells still reach you regardless
  Level 1   = Your own game feedback only: combat results, spell effects, level-ups, item use, command responses
  Level 2   = Level 1, plus shouts (red) from other players, and DM login/logout announcements
  Level 6   = Level 2, plus player logins/logouts, party join/leave, server shutdown warnings
  Level 10  = Level 6, plus chat (blue) from other players. **(default)** 
  Level 11+ = Level 10, plus kill announcements when any player kills a monster

Examples:

  listen    = show your current level
  listen 1  = your own game feedback only; no social channels
  listen 2  = adds shouts; good if the chat channel is busy
  listen 6  = adds logins and party events, but no chat
  listen 10 = default; see all normal messages including chat

Notes:

  * Private tells always reach you, no matter how low your listen level is
  * Shouts carry urgent server-wide messages (admin warnings, etc.); set at least listen 2 to see them
  * Chat is general player conversation; requires listen 10 (the default)
  * Negative values are not accepted
  * No known messages use priority above 10; raising above 11 has no further effect

See also: [help]say[/help]
See also: [help]shout[/help]
See also: [help]chat[/help]
See also: [help]tell[/help]
